cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.AR 

The paper deals with the problem of segmenting curve structures from depth maps, which is a common task in computer vision and graphics. The proposed method is based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are widely used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the exploration of cultural heritage objects, which suggests that it may belong to cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.AR (Augmented Reality). The use of supervised learning algorithms and dense prediction networks indicates that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
